Function: sum_1_m [||g_i(x)||^2]

Constraint: lambda = 1

A stationary convergence occurs in an Extended Kalman Filter with a constraint coefficient.

If x^k describes psi, then in an Extended Kalman Filter:

      x^k=psi
 
      x^{k+1} = x^k - sum_1_m[delg*g]/H

      H = sum_0_k[sum_1_m[delg*g]] + Noise 

A large k simplifies the sums about slope into coefficients (pg 183):

      x^{k+1} = x^k - m[delg*g]/[m(k+1)delg*g]
 
              = x^k - 1/(k+1)

The stepsize diminishes with the limit of k in a denominator and converges!

